Big Fish Small Pond

Owen Phillips

December 12, 2014

Does Superintendent Selection Method Matter? Ideas to change the world

If you were in charge of searching for a new coach to lead the Manchester United Football Club, would you limit your search to only look for potential coaches that are from Manchester? Absolutely not. Youd look for the best canidate for the position regardless of where they came from. But in Mississippi School Districts this is exactly what is happening.

Strangely enough, Mississippi is one of the only states in the country that elects a porition of their district superintendents. Of the 150 or so elected superintendents throughout the country, 63 of them are in Mississippi.

Below is an interactive map that shows the 151 different school districts in Mississippi. The districts colored red are ones that elect their superintendent, while the ones colored green appoint their superintendent.
